  "description": "Small vireo actively foraging during both observations in small / medium deciduous trees in Denver Botanic Gardens. Relatively tame. During observation on the 28th, I encountered the bird after being stopped on a narrow trail by other visitors to the Gardens (who were photographing a rabbit). The bird foraged above us as I waited for the other visitors to finish their photos and pass by. I observed and photographed the bird for 3-5 minutes from about 5 feet away, before other Garden visitors approached and the bird flew into Cheesman.\n\r\nNo vocalizations. \n\r\nYellow flanks & belly. Dark, grayish lores and white above and below eyes.",
